  "notes": "Northern Sotho / Sepedi (Bantu S32), Latin orthography. Seven written vowels: a e ê i o ô u (/a e ɛ i o ɔ u/; the circumflexes are frequently omitted in everyday text, which makes ⟨e⟩ and ⟨o⟩ ambiguous between the close-mid and open-mid values). Digraphs: š /ʃ/, tš /tʃ/, kg /kx/, hl /ɬ/, tlh /tɬʰ/, ng /ŋ/, ny /ɲ/, and the aspirated series ph th kh tsh tšh. Tone (H/L) is phonemic but unwritten and therefore not recoverable from the orthography."
}
